review 1: One of the most comfortable accommodations in Bali. Super nice for those who need quiet place to work/study; good place to rest and relax too üòå beautiful garden and spacious backyard. Pak Ketut and Buk Komang are approachable and kind  ü•∞ üôèüèΩ
review 2: If you are looking for a longer stay in Bali  than this is a good place to stay. Rooms are complete with bed, wifi, tv kitchen and parkingplace.
review 3: Good place to stay, the assistants are there. If you need an assistance, just call the assistant. Rooms are clean, good air circulation. TV+WIFI okay. Near bypass road also.
review 4: A cozy place to stay with a serene neighbourhood. The room is quite big (around 4 x 7 meters) and divided into 2 (bed room and pantry). Bed sheet, blanket and towels are provided. Thanks, pak Nyoman, mbak Desi & pak Latief.
review 5: Good owner, good sanitation best price full facility

name: Katang-Katang Guest House
address: Gg. Taman No.11, Kesiman Kertalangu, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
I highly recommend this place. The atmosphere is cozy, quiet, and like living in nature because you can hear a lot of bird sounds. The place is very clean and outside the room is filled with many plants). For those who like to bathe in unity with nature (whose bathroom conditions are open) it is very suitable to come to this inn.

However, for customers who bring vehicles (especially cars) must ask in advance regarding the availability of parking space because it only fits 1 car. The road to this place is also suitable for 2 cars.
review 2:
This is my first business trip abroad. I spent 15 days staying at Katang-Katang Guest House, which is an excellent and convenient place, giving me the feeling of a traditional Balinese house within a lovely village.

They not only provide accommodation services but are also very supportive and respond promptly to any advice you may need. I felt completely safe and peaceful while living there, making it easy to relax by myself or focus on working during my time there.

I will definitely stay there when I return to Bali in the future. I am 100% satisfied
review 3: Such a nice authentic guest house in Denpasar ! The place is clean and the host are welcoming and helpful!
review 4:
A wonderful place!
We lived here for almost 2 months, we really liked everything!
Very clean, good Wi-Fi, there is a kitchen, a dining area, a green garden and most importantly, very nice hosts!
If in more detail, then:
We were looking for a long-term place to live and work, and it turned out to be perfect!
The hosts were super kind and helpful, they bought a stove and installed another WiFi router!! Therefore, we had a full kitchen, refrigerator, toaster, microwave.
Always very clean, this is carefully monitored. Even the towels smell delicious!
For us, the location was convenient, equally remote from Denpasar and Ubud, there are shops, restaurants and everything you need nearby (5-10 minutes by bike).
The most memorable thing is that the hosts invited us to the ritual of opening a new room!
I highly recommend it!
review 5:
Katang-Katang is actually very conveniently located as there's lots of things to do and good food around if you take a ride.

The owner is so helpful and his son Adi is very trustworthy and he's a travel guru who knows Bali very well so don't be afraid to ask him any questions.

Highly recommended.

name: Warung Nasi Lawar Macho Rena
address: Gg. Taman No.17-14, Kesiman Kertalangu, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
One tips that i would to share to any of you seeking a great food in Bali, especially Lawar and Babi Guling, the more hidden the place, the better it gets.
This place is hidden from the outside world, but a lot of people come here everyday to enjoy the food. For the food is very tasty compared to other lawar we usually see, and it is affordable in which you can request the price of the food.
The best time to visit is around 11-2, but expect a long que for your order
review 2: The rice is good, the seasoning is right, the atmosphere is comfortable, the service is friendly ... .. .

name: Bakmi Ayun 88 Bali
address: Jl. Pucuk Bang Djayanta Residence No.27, Kesiman Kertalangu, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
Amazingly good food and very sweet owner who cooks fresh. The tiny restaurant has one table and is neat and very clean.
The prices are very cheap (25k) for a normal and 35k for a large portion of bakmi Babi.
review 2: A bakmie (noodle) stall in Bali that are operated by owner that are really coming from Tangerang. Noodle quality are excellent especially the Bakmie Lebar (wide noodles). The seasoning looks light but the taste are absolutely amazing!
review 3: Best bakmi!!! The only complain is difficult to park
review 4: The pork bakmi was so good I had another one right after! This place is true to its 5 star rating: delicious fresh noodles, tasty pork, real pork fat soup and a nice and welcoming pak to serve you a cheap & delicious meal. An absolute gem!!
review 5: Coming from Jakarta, we missed having a bowl of good Bakmi Bangka, one of the local delicacy back in Jakarta. I am overjoyed to find the authentic taste in this bowl of noodle. Definitely recommend this place ‚ô•Ô∏è
